name: Homophthalic acid anhydride
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-4505
Reason: 1,2,3,4-Tetrahydroisoquinoline base (106 degrees Celsius) with two carbonyl groups forming a rigid structure and increasing intermolecular interactions. Each carbonyl is estimated to add approximately +20 degrees Celsius due to the formation of a rigid structure and potential hydrogen bonding. Additionally, the tetrahydroisoquinoline base itself has a melting point around 106 degrees Celsius.
